==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dihexagonal
<hw>Di`hex*ag"o*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>hexagonal</ets>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Consisting of two hexagonal parts united; thus, a
<xex>dihexagonal</xex> pyramid is composed of two hexagonal pyramids
placed base to base.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having twelve similar
faces; <as>as, a <ex>dihexagonal</ex> prism</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diiamb</ent>⟦br⟧
